    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-09T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-09T04:00:00-05:00" n="708"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d708">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13312: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-09T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 9, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 9—4:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68. My December 4, 6 p.m. Uncertainty Red destination continues. Main body
                    believed to be in central Hunan. Letter dated Changsha, December 7th, states
                    main body Reds reported to have turned back from Kweichow border for reasons
                    unknown; also that Kwangsi troops have entered Hunan from south and Hupeh troops
                    from north. These troop movements believed are [of] political significance.
                    Hankow military informs me Hupeh troops are proceeding to front via Changsha.
                    American naval authorities holding <hi rend="italic">Monocacy</hi> [at] Hankow
                    in readiness for quick departure for Changsha if necessary, although at present
                    Changsha reported calm.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Department, Peiping, Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
